4forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
This...and...that...
All guys...are distrustful.
Makes me a braggart.

4/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
I haven't seen you before.
Are you a traveler?
If so, then you may have
seen many marvelous things
from near and far.

5PorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
I'm sure you'll probably
be interested in my story.
All the villagers are blockheads,
so they treat me like an idiot.

5forCA.en: I'm not interested in any story.

5/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Indeed... You are not interested...
That's ok.

6PorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
If you change your mind,
you can talk to me whenever.

6forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Good, I have been thinking
that I should tell you this story from the start.

6vorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
You seem to have spent
only a few days here.
Have you ever heard
about The Moving Island?

6/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
In Moscovia,
a story is handed down
from our ancestors, like legends.

7PorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
It is said that
there is an island
which sometimes moves,
not far out at sea.

7forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
But, nobody has seen
this island before.
So, few people have
believed the legend.

7vorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Actually, I thought that
it might be a kind of
old story... nothing more.
But then... I saw...

7/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Actually, I thought that
it might be a kind of
old story... nothing more.
But then... I saw...
The Moving Island!!!

8PorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Surprised? Right...
It is so surprising.
Frankly, you don't believe
any of this story either.

8forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
I saw the island
from the middle of
the village's south shore.

8vorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
At first, I doubted my eyes.
I have never heard that that island really existed here, even though I have lived here all my life!

8/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
I tried to go up
to look at it from
higher ground, but
the island receded
and disappeared...
back to the sea.

9forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
If it does,
one might just think
that they've looked
at an apparition.

9vorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
But a few nights ago...
Finally, the island appeared
in front of me again,
while I was driving my ship to go home.

9/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
At that time, I tried to
get near the island again,
slowly, but it disappeared...
beyond the sea once more.

+PorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
It was then, I couln't help
to finally believe
in the existence of
The Moving Island!

+forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Surely, this must be
a great discovery!
Don't you think??
Doesn't your heart shout out in hopes of adventuring out to the island?

+vorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
I haven't given up yet!
Certainly, it'll appear again
right in front of us!

+/orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
And on that day,
I'll definitely go up to that island... and verify it with my own eyes!

/PorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Clearly, I want to prove
the existence of that island to everyone...

/forCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
If the island appears again,
I should certify its identity.
Would you like to try it?

/vorCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
The best way to find the
island is by direct contact
with a ship in the sea.

//orCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Me?
Of course I have a ship.
Such as I am, I am a fisherman...

APsrCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Ah, you do? You need...
a ship? Hm...too bad.
I can't lend my ship to you...

AfsrCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
But maybe Mr. Ibanoff
can lend his ship to you.
He likes going around
adventuring like me.
He seems to enjoy his youth...

AvsrCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Mr. Ibanoff also traveled and
adventured all over the world,
like you, so he might understand
your sentiments well.

A/srCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
If you want to find the island
by ship, go to Mr. Ibanoff
and ask for a favor.

BfsrCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Are you serious? Did you say
you've found The Moving Island?

BvsrCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
The legend is true!!
I was right, wasn't I?
You must be a great adventurer.

B/srCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Welcome to Moscovia.
What's your impression thus far?
Looks gorgeous, huh?

CPsrCA.en:
[Berbayeff]
Most travelers and strangers
like our village.
I want you to visit places here and there. You'll probably love this town.

C/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Yes. I am Mr. Ibanoff.
What's up?

DvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You are an adventurer, right?
You come from a strange land?
Well, well, well...
You are welcome here.

D/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
When I adventured around
Rune Midgarts, maybe it was
well before you were born.
Ah... I miss those days...

EPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Now, I'm so tired;
my body and my heart.
I get reminded of fond
memories just by looking at the sea...

EfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Um... Stories...
What to talk about first?
Right, I'll talk about that time I fought against a huge flock of Porings...

E/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You'll be happy that you
listened to the adventure story.
Well, well, well...
When I was 24 years old...
My colleagues and I were passing by a forest near Payon...

GPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I did a very good
job in the fight, so
my colleagues and I were
able to get back safely.

GfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What did you think?
Next... Let's talk about
the haunting of a Goblin mob...!

HPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If not...Ooo, I can just
keep going and going...
No? Too bad... Hehe...
Let's talk next time.

HfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Yeah? Ohohoh... my friend,
we are in sync with each other...!

HvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Ok, this time I'll talk
about the bloody fight at the haunting of a Goblin mob...

IvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
So, the day's great bloody
fight was over like that... Ohwee...

I/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hah! You are the first
to listen carefully to
my stories, for a long time.
Feels so good...

JPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You absolutely have talent,
as a great adventurer.
You can become a good friend to me.

JfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Next time, we talk about your
adventure story... eh? ~
If you ever need anything,
come talk to me whenever, hahaha!

JvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Ah! The good listener!
What will you do if you
borrow my ship? I wonder...

J/srCA.en:
[{}]
I'm going to adventure out
to sea, to find a moving
island which has brought
many a legend to this neighboring village.

KPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
The Moving Island?
I have never seen that really...
You are young! Hawhawhaw!

KfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I hope that you find
the island without fail,
and that you bring back
surprising news to us!

KvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Let it be so!
First, I should check
the state of the ship...
You have some work to do,
if you want to help me.

K/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
She has not floated
for a long time,
so we should check
and repair the parts
that power her up.

LPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Preparing the tools for repairs, in this place, takes several days... if you can possible prepare them.

LfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
The materials needed are:
^0000FFStrange Steel Piece 10, Rusty Screw 10, Flexible Tube 5, Jubilee 10^000000.

LvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
When you've prepared all the materials, bring them to me. I'll repair the ship.

L/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You want to borrow
my ship so spontaneously??
I don't even know you!!
You are more rude than you look.

MPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I don't know, how you know
that I have a ship...
Anyway, I can't lend my ship willingly to strangers.

MfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Did you bring all the materials?
If we have all the materials,
we can prepare for departure!

MvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh! You got the materials.
It's enough.

M/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Okay, we are at the ready.
When would you like to depart?
I'll say one thing...
It's difficult to keep this
ship afloat after high-tide.

NPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
In these neighboring waters,
there are many raging waves.
During high-tide, sailing does not get any easier... even for an expert seaman.

NfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Remember, the poor condition of this ship also factors when attempting to plow through the raging waves.

NvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If you are ready to depart, tell me, and we can check the tides.

N/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
These materials are insufficient.
Perhaps you forgot some of them?

OPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh. Are you ready to depart?
Good, let's see...

OfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hmm. It's not a bad time.
We should hurry up
while the tides are low.
The ship is prepared already
at a dock nearby, so we can depart right away.

OvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Gee. The tide is too high.
It's too dangerous to depart
right now because of the waves getting too rugged.

O/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
When the sea calms down a bit, you can come back. We can't depart right now.

PPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
That last sailing was tough...
But, all adventures
are like that...
Hahaha!

PfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If you keep a mind to
depart again... tell me
and we can check the tides.

QfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
When you are ready to depart, tell me.

QvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey you... You are alive!
When you were swept away by the waves, I thought that was the last I would ever see of you!

Q/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Anyway, where were you all this time? What happened to you after you fell into the sea?

RfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh... that's really marvelous.
Well I never...
The island truly exists...?

RvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What's more...
The island is not an island?!?
It's a gigantic whale???

R/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
And tress grow... and water streams... along the whale's back!!?

SPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
That's unbelievable!
The most marvelous incident I have ever heard in my lifetime!

SfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Also, I am surprised at the presence of an aged person on Whale Island!

SvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
He must be a man strong in spirit... with experience and high discipline.

S/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
The story of the island has
advanced enough until this part.
Why don't you announce your
findings to our dearest Csar
and receive aid to find Whale Island?

TPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Our dear Csar likes it very
much to hear stories about
valuable things, so if he
listens to your story, he may give you a prize...

TfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
And if you have any plans to go back to the island, I want to go together with you! Eh? Hahaha!

TvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If our dear Csar listens to this kind of story, he would find it a pleasure.

T/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
He might even give you a prize...

UPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hm. Our dear Csar requested evidence of the whale island?...

UfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
That may prove a little difficult...

UvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Do you have a guarantee that you can find Whale Island again?

U/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I think you won't give up.
What about if we depart
once more, and I will gladly help you find Whale Island!

VPsrCA.en: Try again to find Whale Island.

VvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
That does it! I expected it.
I knew you weren't the type to give up an adventure!

V/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Again, let's get the ship ready and sail before high-tide!

WPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I see...
Even though you like adventure,
it might be impossible to find Whale Island again...

WfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If you change your mind,
anytime, come tell me.
Frankly, I would love to see you prove the existence of Whale Island to our dear Csar.

WvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh! Are you ready to depart?

W/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What a surprise!!
Where have you been??
I was worried that you had disappeared forever!

XPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I don't care... Wherever you have been, it's very good to see you again.

XfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I can guess you'd like to go to Whale Island once again...

XvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh. You came back!
So, how did you do?

X/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You say...
If you bring the materials, the old man makes the instrument...

YPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
And he promised that he won't move the island until you go back again...

YfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I see. I remember the exact directions. Let's leave immediately, as soon as you are ready.

YvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh. Did you get the all the materials you needed?

Y/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If so, do you want to go now?

ZfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I see. I will wait.

Z/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Finally, everything has ended successfully. With this, I add 1 more page to my... no, OUR adventure story!

aPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Someday, I want to have another chance to have another fantastic adventure with a person like you!

afsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I heard that you played a great performance, with the instrument from Whale Island, at the Imperial Palace. Eh? You must have quite the talent!

avsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What's going on?
You need a ship right now? Let's get ready to leave. Hurry up!

a/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You are also an adventurer from another province. I also was a great adventurer.

bPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Uf...I just want to be 20 years younger, so I can travel here and there with invigorating youth such as you... Time is an enemy. Hahahahaha!

bfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What a time for sailing!
The wind of the sea is so cool.

bvsrCA.en:
[{}]
You didn't have to accompany me through this dangerous sailing...

b/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Such as I am, I know the
sea a lot better than you!
And this ship has been my
friend through all my life!
I wouldn't abandon a friend.
Would you? ~

cPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I will order you where to go, by watching the seas.

cfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You just adjust the direction of the rudder by following my orders.

cvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
At first, hold the rudder to go forward, to the east.

c/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Keep the direction by holding the rudder to move forward to the East.

dPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hm. The sea currents have changed. Adjust the rudder forward to the North, to follow the currents.

dfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Nothing yet... Nothing has changed in the flow of water. There is nothing of note...

dvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
We had better keep sailing on this heading for now.

d/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
We must first repulse the monsters!

ePsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey!
Did you not hear me?
Change the rudder forward to the North, and follow the currents!

efsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hm. The sea currents have changed. Adjust the rudder forward to the East, to follow the currents.

evsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hm. The sea currents have changed. Adjust the rudder forward to the West, to follow the currents.

e/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hm. The sea currents have changed. Adjust the rudder forward to the South, to follow the currents.

fPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey!
Did you not hear me?
Change the rudder forward to the East, and follow the currents!

ffsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey!
Did you not hear me?
Change the rudder forward to the West, and follow the currents!

fvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey!
Did you not hear me?
Change the rudder forward to the South, and follow the currents!

f/srCA.en: Hm. The sea currents have changed. Adjust the rudder forward to the West, to follow the currents.

gPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
We should make sure to kill any monsters onboard.

gfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Look... Beyond the sea!
Do you see something moving mysteriously?

gvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Heheh... What is...
that... Hey! You...
Go around the deck to look more carefully! Go!

g/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What are you doing...? Go around the deck to look more carefully! Go!

hPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
This time, I hope to find that whale island again without any incidents...

hfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
The method is the same as before.

h/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Look there!
There is a moving island!
We have done well!

iPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh...my...
It really is there...
A whale! It's unbelievable!
It is as true as that...

ifsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I feel I can go anywhere with you! Even through impossible things! Haha! You are a friend who brings good luck.

ivsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Okay, now that you have landed on the island, I have to go back...

i/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
If another wave crashes against this boat, I feel she might break into pieces!

jPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Good luck. I hope you
can return without problems.
I will pray for you.
See you next time.

jfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Don't adjust the rudder now.
Wait for my direction.

jvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
What? How did you get on
this ship??? You... No.
I'll forgive you this once, but go back now.

lfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Good. Firstly, we should
keep heading east this way.
When I give the order,
please adjust the rudder again.

lvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I said that we should go East!
You should sail in the right direction! To the east!

l/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You don't have to adjust
the rudder for now.
Wait for my direction.

mPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Do not yet adjust the rudder.
Only when I order you to,
you adjust the rudder.

mfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I said that we should go North!
You should sail in the right direction! To the north!

mvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Oh no! Monsters have appeared!
Let's get ready to fight! Hurry!

m/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Good. Firstly, we should
keep heading north this way.
When I give the order,
please adjust the rudder again.

nPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Wait! Something has appeared in front of us...

nvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
These monsters are like none I have ever encountered! Be careful! We must repulse these monsters!

n/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I said that we should go West!
You should sail in the right direction! To the west!

oPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Good. Firstly, we should
keep heading west this way.
When I give the order,
please adjust the rudder again.

ofsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I said that we should go South!
You should sail in the right direction! To the south!

ovsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Good. Firstly, we should
keep heading south this way.
When I give the order,
please adjust the rudder again.

pPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
I said that you go to the north.
You should sail in the right direction! To the north!

pfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
You can adjust the rudder,
under my direction.

pvsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey! Listen to what I am saying. How come you go there without my permission...

qfsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Hey {}! Look!
It's dangerous! Hide! Hurry!

rPsrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Watch out! {}!
Ah... That...That is... What...

r/srCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Now that all the monsters are gone, we can start sailing again normally.

tPsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You're carrying too many items. Please come back after using a kafra service.

tfsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Oh, you wake.
How do you feel? Are you ok??

t/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Well... You were a bit
of a surprise! I haven't
talked for a long time...
with a person who lives on dry land.

uPsrCA.en:
[{}]
Where am I?
Who are you old man?

ufsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
This is... well...
What can I say...
This is called a moving island, by most people.

uvsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
This is a small island that only I inhabit.

u/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I call it...
Whale Island.

vPsrCA.en:
[{}]
This place is very famously known as The Moving Island! But... This island is... Maybe...

vfsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Now do you get it? Hahaha!
Right. We are standing on
the back of a gigantic whale!
That's why I call it Whale Island!

vvsrCA.en:
[{}]
How...? How is it possible
that the water flows in streams here? And trees grow! On the whale's back!?!

v/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Heheheh. This is an island
of legend. Right now you are
experiencing greatness! Hahahaha!

wfsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Heheh, as you can see,
I am just an aged man.
I've simply spent my lifetime here leisurely, by breaking off relations with any unworldly life.

wvsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Okay, now you get yourself together. I will send you back to dry land. If you don't go back soon, some people may worry.

w/srCA.en: -The island starts to move slowly when the old man plays an unfamiliar instrument...-

xPsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
In a few minutes, you will go back to the land from whence you came. You can relax.

xfsrCA.en:
-The old man starts to play
his instrument, with eyes closed.
He is unresponsive...
like having fallen into a world only his own.-

xvsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Hm... Almost there...
Young man, you will arrive back on the mainland in a few minutes. Go carefully.

x/srCA.en:
[{}]
Old man, if I want to come back here again, how can I do it?

yPsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Hehe... Do you want to come here again? Here? Where I live alone? In this small island? You are funny...

yfsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If we are preordained to meet,
we will meet here again,
won't we? Heheheh...

yvsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
It's time to... well,
go back safely. Someday, if you want to come again to meet me, you can endure the same seas as last time. I won't stop you. Hehehe.

y/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Hahaha... I didn't know that I would meet you again! How did you return?

zPsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Hm... just like that?
Whoever hasn't come here directly
would expect you to return like that. Well.

zfsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I just wanted to spend the rest of my life here, leisurely... I'm interested in the world... but I'm no match for it...

zvsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Do not look sorry for me.
When you went back I didn't ask you not to say anything about this island to others.

z/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If I had decided to hide where nobody can find me... Well, you needn't worry too much about that now.

0PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Anyway, are you troubled?
What are you going to do?

0/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Do that. Think carefully, the answer is to be found... Hoohoohoo!

1PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
To bring the Csar here and show him everything?!? It's difficult...

1fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
An evidence of whale island...
That's all you need if only it existed in this island...

1vsrCA.en: -The aged man closes his eyes and starts to play his instrument, as he falls in thought.-

1/srCA.en:
[{}]
Old man, could you make one of those instruments for me? That is a marvelous thing that I've seen only here.

2PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Oh... That's a good idea.
There isn't an instrument like this in all Moscovia! Absolutely...

2fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Hm... If you grant my request, I will make this instrument for you.

2/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Just in time. I have always used this instrument which is already over 50 years old. The body is so worn. It's not surprising that it's falling apart...

3PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
It is made with strings that only exist in this place, but you can get the other materials for it in the mainland.

3fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If you bring the materials, I can make a new one.

3vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
The materials are ^0000FFLog 30, Tough Vines 20, Antelope Horn 20, Sea-otter Fur 10^000000.

3/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I won't move the island, so you can find it when you come back with the materials.

4PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Tell me whenever you're ready, and I'll send you back to the mainland.

4fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Okay, are you ready to go back to the mainland?

5PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You should bring these materials:

5fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You should bring these materials:
^0000FFLog 30, Tough Vines 20, Antelope Horn 20, Sea-otter Fur 10^000000.

5vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I see. If so, let's go.

5/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Oh... Did you get all the materials?

6PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You found the right materials.
Okay, I will start to make the instrument.

6fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Wait for a moment until I make the instrument successfully.

6vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Ugh... We need more materials...
We need ^0000FFLog 30, Tough Vines 20, Antelope Horn 20, Sea-otter Fur 10^000000.

6/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
What will you do? Will you go back to the mainland to find the materials?

7PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I have succeeded in making the instrument! Here you are. It's yours.

7fsrCA.en:
This instrument is called a Gusli.
This is a traditional instrument which comes from a faraway land of the ancestors of Moscovia.

7vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I am the last person who has learned it in this land.

7/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
So, indeed... This is a very special item here, that only we have.

8PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If you show this to the good Csar, he can believe your story about the island. Everything is going to be well.

8fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
So, what will you do now?

8vsrCA.en: How would I get back here?

8/srCA.en: I want to learn the Gusli.

9fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You are my friend now,
and you have this instrument.
Whenever you want to come back
here again, just play the Gusli
at the docks of Moscovia.

9vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Even if it's difficult to play it well, because you may not yet know how to play it, it's not a problem. Just make a sound.

9/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
This island... this whale... can perceive the sound of a Gusli from an endless distance away.

+PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If you play this instrument, wherever you are, I'll go to you with this island. Only if you are a friend... heheh.

+fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You really want to...
learn this instrument...
don't you?
Well... it's hard to learn
in such a short time...

+vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
It's okay if you can't play this instrument. I already made it for you.

+/srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
But I can teach you how
to play it anyway.
I can't be too sure, though
because I have never taught others.

/PsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Okay. If you ready to play the Gusli, let me know.

/fsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I see. Okay, let's go.

/vsrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Whenever you want to come back here again, play the Gusli at the docks of Moscovia.

//srCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
It's not completed yet. Wait for it.

APwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Well, what will you do now?

AfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Are you ready to learn the Gusli?
Please equip the Gusli.

AvwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Hm... Very well.
At first, look at me how I play, then you play it slowly.

A/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Do not hurry,
keep your composure,
just look carefully,
and follow me slowly.

BPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Oh! Ooh... Your hands are really good. You are surely talented with a music instrument.

BfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
I heard that there are some adventurers in the mainland... that like playing instruments and singing songs! You must be one of them.

BvwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
This may go faster than I expected...

B/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Okay, it's time for your turn. Play it. Play the song that I played.

CPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Oh! You are good at playing the Gusli! In such a short time... you are great!

CfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
You've done well. I don't need to teach you any more. Your ability will be improved with more practice.

CvwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Now go back to the mainland and play the Gusli for our dear Csar.

C/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
With your ability to play, surely you can win the admiration of all.

DPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Um, a little bit greenhorn...
Do not play that way.
Take more time to concentrate while you play.

DfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Practice more on your own.
I will check on you again.
If you practice, you will be good at it in no time.

DvwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
[Aged Stranger]
Oh! You are good at playing the Gusli! In such a short time... you are great!

D/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Um... Your preparations are not good. You're not holding the instrument correctly. Equip it properly, and then you can learn.

EPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Tell me again when you are prepared to play the Gusli correctly.

EfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Are you ready to learn the Gusli?

E/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
With your ability, you can absolutely play it wonderfully. Cheer up!

FPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Okay, let's play again.
Play the song that I played.

FfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Good. Let's play again. Play the song that I played.

FvwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If you play the tune which you have just learned, I'll come to see you, even if I'm far away.

F/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Long time, no see!
You probably like the island, don't you?
Please stay and take a rest.

GPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Or if you want, I can send you back to the mainland. What'll it be?

G/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Well, well... Do as you please.
If so, I will take a rest.

HPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Oh, if you want, I can
guide you to a good place for you.

HfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
There are some lands...
untouched and mysterious...
around Moscovia...

HvwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
If you want, I'll send you there. What do you think of that?

IfwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
This is Whale Island.
I don't know how you came to be here.

I/wrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Heheh... You do that.
I'll take a rest.

JPwrCA.en:
[Aged Stranger]
Okay. I will take you back right away.

JvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
You!!!
So many people saw you
meet the Baba Yaga!

J/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
The guilt which must be felt, when meeting secretly with a witch...

KPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
For that, we indict capital punishment without any just trial!

KfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
But you are a stranger to these lands... So I will hold you in special trial.

KvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
If you have anything to say... spare me no detail.

LPwrCA.en: -Talk about what happened with Baba Yaga, and move forward with the plan.-

LfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Hm-hm, that's an embarrassing story... But if you are telling the truth, my people will be pleased.

LvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Okay, bring to me
any evidence, to believe
what you are saying.

L/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
You killed the Baba Yaga!!
If this is true, bring
me Yaga's Pestles.
If you do, I will make
sure no one ever doubts you.

NPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Hm.You do have evidence.
In advance, I will recognize the first part of your actions.

NfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
But I can't trust
in you wholly.

NvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I can grant special forgiveness
to whom has hunted Baba Yaga.
But above that, if you perform
any doubtable actions,
I will arrest you immediately,
and go back to punishing you in an instant!

N/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Otherwise, when you succeed with the magic that holds the summer, announce it to me immediately.

OPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Did you listen, stranger?
If you bring
40 of Yaga's Pestles,
from Baba Yagas,
I won't doubt you one bit.

OfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
You're carrying too many items.
Please come after using a Kafra service.

OvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
[Csar Aleksay III]
You!!!
So many people saw you
meet the Baba Yaga!

O/wrCA.en:
Did you listen, stranger?
If you bring
40 of Yaga's Pestles,
from Baba Yagas,
I won't doubt you one bit.

PPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Did you bring some evidence to resolve your issue of doubt, traveler?

P/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Good,
I won't doubt you any more.
Because you've proven yourself,
you can remain a free traveler.

QPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Surely, I hate cooperating with Baba Yaga.
But if my people are happy
after the work you do,
I am also pleased.

QfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
For the time being, I will admit that you are coming and going to hunt Baba Yaga.

QvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
But do not engage in doubtable behavior that would instigate my people to act in a strange way!

Q/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
If you do that, I will arrest you immediately!
So take care of yourself.

RPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Your items do not match the
count of 40 Yaga's Pestles.
Did you forget the amount,
or did you wish to lie to me...

RfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I will treat that as a joke!
A kind of sarcasm!
You go away now and bring some evidence to certify your innocence.

RvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I said to bring me
40 Yaga's Pestles
from the Baba Yaga.

R/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Are you here to tease me?

SPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
It'd be great if I stayed put, for the good of both me and my people. I don't want to see the Baba Yaga personally.

SfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
So, I want you to
take my place for that.

SvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Please help Baba Yaga
to seize the summer.

S/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Are you here for...

TPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I already heard about the
weather from the minister.

TfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Actually, I was a little
dissatisfied with the doing
of witchcraft at the center
of the square...

TvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
But... I can admit it was good work.

T/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Everyone hates the cold winter.
Now, the winter will not
come anymore! So, I'm very
pleased.

UPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Right.
I want to give you something
in the name of the people.

UfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Here, take it.
I give it as an atonement
to make my people happy.

UvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Stay here as long as you want, and enjoy yourself to the fullest this summer!

U/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Welcome to Moscovia!
I am the ruler, Csar Aleksay III, of Moscovia.

VPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Go back to your hometown and talk about the beauty of Moscovia! Talk about my great government to all the people of the lands!

VfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
A foreign traveler...?
Do you have something to tell me?

VvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
If it is not important,
have an audience with the Prime Minister first.

V/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh, are you the traveler who told me about an interesting adventure story...

WPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Not only are you not from Moscovia, but also... you have found the moving island, which only existed in legends! I want to hear details...

WfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Let's hear it.
Tell me quickly.
I'm anxious to know the truth about the island.

X/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Surely, an interesting story... But it sounds so unbelievable! What do you think, Prime Minister?

YPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
It doesn't sound like a lie,
but it's difficult to believe
completely. I mean, I've known
a whale to be huge, but...

YfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
...a person living there...
water streaming...
and a tree growing on it...!!!
Hmm...

YvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I agree. I have heard many kinds of mysterious adventure stories, but this sounds like an absurd story!

Y/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Not to mention that it's happened near my nation. Unbelievable!

ZPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
But Csar... In my memory,
I heard that exactly, the
last time a story was told
about the mysterious moving island. But there was a musical instrument...which an old man played...

ZfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Really? Tell me the details.

ZvwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Surely, I have heard the same
story, as told in the legends
of our ancestors; about an old man who lived there.

Z/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Hm. There are many doubtful points. Ordinarily, I would give you a big prize, but in this case, it is difficult to believe.

aPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Bring me something to prove
the existence of the whale.
If you do, I will give you a big prize.

afwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
But if you don't,
I will punish you for your lies! Bring this instrument that supposedly an old man has.

avwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Csar... This is a foreigner...
No disrespect was meant to you.
Perhaps a little more generosity is in order?

a/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
No way! If the story is not true, many other foreign travelers who pass by this land will disrespect me like this... What would you have me do?

bfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
You got it, traveler?
You have a heavy responsibility.
Bring evidence of this whale island to me, to provide me with some relief. Now go.

bvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I'm tired... I want to take a rest, so... leave.

b/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Just think about finding the whale island...

cPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh. You've come back...
Hm. Did you find something to bring to me from the whale island?

cfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Did you bring the instrument?
A Gooselri? Which only exists
in the whale island? Let's see.

cvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh... Is this instrument... a Gooselri...?

c/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Actually, Csar, I believe it is called a Gusli.

dPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh. Prime Minister, is this the correct instrument from the legends, then?

dfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I can't be sure, but this is definitely an instrument never seen in our lands before.

dvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Hm. This is also my first time seeing this kind of musical instrument. So mysterious... Hey! Can you play it?

efwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
You can play it!
Good, play it right away!

evwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Um...What is this? Do you mock me? You are so impudent... You...!

e/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Csar... Calm down, please.
If you are quick to anger by such a lowly person, it will become a problem of prestige for you.

fPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Agh... I agree with you.
You. Give a proper prize to the adventurer and send them on their way.

ffwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
How can I re...reward...?

fvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I ordered you instead Prime Minister, to make this poor player disappear from in front of my eyes, right now.

f/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
You should be grateful for the Csar's mercy... impudent traveler...

gPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I regard your efforts... and I reward you. Take this and leave.

gfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Um... That's too bad.
I see... Will I ever believe...

gvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Thanks for your efforts.
Hey, Prime Minister,
reward this traveler.

g/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
How can I reward the traveler?

hPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I leave the matter in your hands; it's up to you. I will take a rest.

hfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
The Csar didn't take pleasure in your story, as I expected.

hvwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
However, I regard your efforts... and I reward you. Take this.

h/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
What are you doing? Can you play it without even holding the musical instrument???

iPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Don't be impudent with me! Do it right!

ifwrCA.en:
[{}]
Yes. I learned how to play it at Whale Island.

ivwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh! Oh!... You can play it!
Play it right away. I wonder about its sound.

i/wrCA.en: -When the music of the Gusli is played, all the people in the Csar's Palace fall in with the tune.-

jPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh! I can't hear without tears.
That's a sad tune.

jfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
That's right, Csar.
I have never heard a sad tune such as this.
Kh-huk. Sniff.

jvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Huk... You. Give a big prize to this traveler!

j/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Hukhuk... Sniff. How can I reward this?

kPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
I leave this matter in your hands.
Give a proper prize to whom has shown me a great story and beautiful music.

kfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I express thanks to you on behalf of our dear Csar and all the people in his palace. I will reward your efforts, in the name of the Csar.

kvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
But you... Where do you keep the instrument which you are to show me?

k/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Don't you need to be holding the instrument, in order to play it???

lPwrCA.en:
[{}]
I'm sorry. I will be ready now, and try again to play it.

lfwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
What... If you have special things to attend to, leave.

lvwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Um... You are a traveler, as I see. If you have special things to attend to, don't interfere with my rest.

l/wrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Oh... You. ~
Nice to see you again.
I want for you to sometimes stop by here and play some music for me. ~

mPwrCA.en:
[Csar Aleksay III]
Traveler, welcome to Moscovia!
I am its ruler... the Csar! Aleksay the Third!

mvwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
You are in trouble if
you conspire against the Csar,
so, make your actions carefully,
and if you want to clean yourself from suspicion... do everything you can to prove your innocence.

m/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
You have just cleared your name, but... we don't trust you wholly yet.

nPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I can't trust you, but...
if you succeed in taking hold of the summer... I might be able to.

nfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
We know that you mean well.
But we can't fully trust you,
so we kept an eye on your movements.

nvwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I heard that you performed witchcraft at the palace square... so, I ordered scholars to investigate the weather.

n/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
The results from taking observation of the weather, are the reducing change of temperature, and that the highest temperature is now stabilized.

oPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I don't know what this may mean, by way of principle, but I've decided to admit the facts.

ofwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Already, our dear Csar knows.
I finished the report.
Go and announce it to him.

ovwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
You are a foreign traveler. This is the Moscovia Palace, home of Csar Aleksay the Third. Extending your every courtesy here... is not bad manners.

o/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Traveler, why have you come to the Csar's Palace?

pvwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
If so... look around with caution. Do not bother the Csar.

p/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Moscovia welcomes all travelers such as yourself!

qPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Marvelously, our dear Csar likes it very much when interesting stories are often told to him.

qfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Did you come to see our dear Csar? If so, tell me your business with him in advance.

q/wrCA.en: I have an adventure story for him.

rPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I will tell him directly about your business. You don't need to worry yourself with the Csar.

rfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I wonder what sort of things have happened to you... The Csar will be very pleased to hear your stories.

rvwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I will admit you. If our dear Csar is satisfied with your story, he will give you a big prize.

r/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I already announced you,
so go see him and speak to him directly.

sPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Now, our dear Csar needs a rest.
You should do your duty and go find the whale island.

sfwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Ah! You've come back.
I will request for you to see him immediately.

svwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
I don't want to hear your terrible
performance anymore, so... go away.

s/wrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
May I help you? Our dear Csar is taking a rest. If you have no special business with him, please come back later.

tPwrCA.en:
[Prime Minister Dmitree]
Your Gusli performance was so touching. Unforgettable! Whenever you are here, please allow us to hear that tune again.

tfwrCA.en: -Watching the sea from the docks, it suddenly dawns upon you that you have memories from Whale Island.-

ufwrCA.en: -Slowly, your hands are on the Gusli, and the playing starts... reminding you of the melody which the aged stranger had played...-

uvwrCA.en:
[Village Resident]
So...something is rising from the sea!!!

vPwrCA.en:
[Mr. Ibanoff]
Ohohoh!... That's the whale island...!!! Someday, I hope to go there! Hahaha.

vfwrCA.en:
[{}]
Oh my goodness... Slipped right out of my mind... to forget equipping the Gusli.

vvwrCA.en:
[{}]
The aged stranger said that when I want to go to Whale Island again, I should play the Gusli from this place...

v/wrCA.en:
[{}]
I can go some other time.
I will do other work now.

wfwrCA.en:
Wait a moment!!
You have too many items.
You can't receive this.
Lighten your weight and
try again.

wvwrCA.en:
[Irina]
Hello, foreign traveler!
Have you had good day
in Moscovia?

w/wrCA.en:
[Irina]
A special souvenir for visiting Moscovia...?

xPwrCA.en:
[Irina]
For you, let's make a Shafka hat. The Shafka has practicality and it's spruce! Do you want one?

x/wrCA.en:
[Irina]
When I look at you, you seem to want to put on something of a thick fur hat on your head, out in this temperature. A Shafka!

yPwrCA.en:
[Irina]
If you've come here for the first time, you might not know... that winter here is famous for being so long and cold in Moscovia.

yfwrCA.en:
[Irina]
A Shafka hat is especially necessary to live here during the cold seasons. Without this hat, you may not endure a winter!

yvwrCA.en:
[Irina]
Now, the long, long winter has ended and the sun is shining... But someday the winter will come again. So, for preparation, you should keep a Shafka hat handy.

y/wrCA.en:
[Irina]
Don't worry about keeping warm if you're wearing a Shafka hat. Even during the coldest weather... You can roll around in the snow and the Shafka still keeps you warm!

zPwrCA.en:
[Irina]
Do you want to make a Shafka hat?
Heheh. Good idea!
That's a good task.
You will be grateful forever.

zfwrCA.en:
[Irina]
If you bring the materials,
we can make one immediately!
The materials are: ^0000FFNine Tails 20, Yarn 10, Soft Silk 10, Sea-otter Fur 20, Spool 1^000000.

zvwrCA.en:
[Irina]
You did well.
Give me the materials. I will make the Shafka.

z/wrCA.en:
[Irina]
Good, I made it. So, how about it? Do you like it?

0PwrCA.en:
[Irina]
If you need a Shafka hat,
come to me whenever,
with the materials.
I will make it.

0vwrCA.en:
[Irina]
Ah... You lack some materials. We can't make the Shafka hat with just these materials.

0/wrCA.en:
[Irina]
If you bring the right materials, I will make a Shafka immediately.

1PwrCA.en:
[Irina]
The materials are: ^0000FFNine Tails 20, Yarn 10, Soft Silk 10, Sea-otter Fur 20, Spool 1^000000.

[Charabel Schedule]
NOTICE, due to the varying
tides here in Moscovia,
the Charabel can only
depart when the tide is low.
